cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.CR, cs.DC 

This paper discusses the challenges of delivering massive content over wireless networks, which falls under the category of network infrastructure and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of information-centric networking (ICN) and content rate maximization, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for security and privacy in content delivery, which falls under the category of cryptography (cs.CR) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
